# CODEOWNERS — source of truth for critical paths and review ownership
#
# This file feeds two systems:
#   1. GitHub's "Require review from Code Owners" branch protection rule.
#   2. The risk-rail CI gate (`pr-rail-guard` or equivalent): any PR declared
#      `green` that touches a path listed here fails the gate. See
#      `WORKFLOW.md §5 — Risk rail enforcement at L`.
#
# Conventions:
#   - One critical zone per line. Wildcards welcome.
#   - The owner can be a GitHub username, a team, or a placeholder for solo
#     repos (e.g. `@yourhandle`).
#   - Keep this list aligned with `AGENTS.md §Critical zones`.
#   - When you remove a path here, write an ADR explaining why (you're
#     lowering the bar for an entire zone — that's a decision).

# Universal critical paths (almost always):
package.json                                    @<owner>
package-lock.json                               @<owner>
.github/CODEOWNERS                              @<owner>
.github/workflows/                              @<owner>

# Agent harness (changes affect every agent's behaviour):
AGENTS.md                                       @<owner>
CLAUDE.md                                       @<owner>
WORKFLOW.md                                     @<owner>
.agents/                                        @<owner>
scripts/                                        @<owner>
agents/                                         @<owner>     # Codex Desktop / external-tool install metadata (if shipped)

# Project-specific critical zones — REPLACE these with your real paths:
# Examples:
# src/engine/                                   @<owner>
# src/auth/                                     @<owner>
# src/db/migrations/                            @<owner>
# worker/src/                                   @<owner>

# Documentation (lighter ownership, but agent-readable docs touch many systems):
docs/adr/                                       @<owner>
